description: The other "Nana" of the series, alongside Oosaki Nana , this Nana comes to Tokyo looking to find her dream. Unlike Oosaki, however, she comes from a large and happy household, though her childish outlook prevents her from living on her own initially. She always falls in love at first sight . Due to her kindness and faithfulness, Oosaki Nana nicknames her "Hachi," after the dog Hachikou. Additionally, "hachi" means the number "eight" in Japanese, while "nana" is one reading for "seven".
name: Komatsu Nana
